PresentationVariable.Name: UBO

Title.Formula: "There is a clear understanding of ultimate beneficial owner(s) UBOs"

PresentationVariable.Hint: A UBO is a natural person with the actual control within a company / institution by: [BR][/BR] a) >25% capital interest [BR][/BR] b) >25% of voting rights as a shareholder or otherwise [BR][/BR] c) >25% beneficiary of a foundation's equity [BR][/BR] d) >25% specific control over the equity of the foundation [BR][/BR] [BR][/BR] There are three key questions that will help you to determine the UBO: [BR][/BR] a) Who makes the decisions? Who really pulls the strings? [BR][/BR] b) Who has >25% of capital contributed [BR][/BR] c) Who has >25% of voting rights. [BR][/BR] Beneficial Owners for Unincorporated Trusts are every beneficiary that it has been determined will benefit from at least 25% of the trust property and all Trustees. The 25% rule does not apply to Trustees. [BR][/BR] In the case of a partnership (other than a limited liability partnership), beneficial owner means any individual who:[BR][/BR] (a) Ultimately is entitled to or controls (whether the entitlement or control is direct or indirect) more than a 25% share of the capital or profits of the partnership or more than 25% of the voting rights in the partnership, or [BR][/BR] (b) Otherwise exercises control over the management of the partnership.

PresentationVariable.Name: Boughtup
PresentationVariable.Hint: This is not easy to find. [BR][/BR] If you run your internet check and find information that the BV is offered for sale. Then it is immediately apparent. [BR][/BR] It can also be that the relation itself hands you the deed of shares transfer as an attachment of the statutes. But if you don't have evidence that the BV is bought up, then you don't need to actively ask the client. [BR][/BR] Why is medium risk? [BR][/BR] Previously you had to have a 'declaration of no objection' in order to establish a bv. People who were not able to receive such a declaration (e.g. due to a fraud conviction) the only other option was to buy a bv. [BR][/BR] Nowadays the declaration is no longer needed.
